721129f-a.text:
Liberty Street, north side, between Greenwich and
Washington Streets, showing a 9 foot alley between No's 129 and 131 which according to the City Record appears to have no owner. Its is 72 feet deep and of irregular width, leading to the rear of buildings that face on the west side of Greenwich Street. At the northern extremity is the side of the building in which John Thomas Smith lived and recently died; No. 154 Greenwich Street.
August 1938

George D. Chinn
